description: The SL7i-BL sound suppressor, installed on compatible BoreLock muzzle brakes. Manufactured by Ase Utra.

name: Sako TRG PGM Precision .338 LM sound suppressor
description: A sound suppressor manufactured by PGM Precision, designed to fit .338 Lapua Magnum weapons.

name: CGS Hekate DT .338 LM sound suppressor
description: The Hekate DT .338 LM suppressor boasts great noise and flash reduction for large caliber rifles. Manufactured by CGS Group.

name: Ase Utra BoreLock .338 LM muzzle brake
description: A muzzle brake manufactured by Ase Utra for .338 LM (8.6x70). Reduces recoil and counters the muzzle rise. The brake is threaded and compatible with BoreLock-type sound suppressors.

name: Ase Utra BoreLock thread protector
description: A threading protection cap for Ase Utra BoreLock muzzle brakes.

name: Sako TRG .338 LM thread protector
description: A threading protection cap for the Sako TRG .338 LM rifle barrel.

name: Sako TRG Coretac CoreBrake .338 LM muzzle brake
description: A .338 LM muzzle brake for the TRG sniper rifle. Manufactured by Coretac Solutions.

name: Sako TRG 22/42/M10 .338 LM muzzle brake
description: A TRG .338 LM sniper rifle muzzle brake, manufactured by Sako.

name: Sako TRG M10 .338 LM 20 inch barrel
description: A 20 inch (508mm) .338 Lapua Magnum barrel for the TRG M10 sniper rifle, manufactured by Sako.

name: Sako TRG M10 .338 LM 27 inch barrel
description: A 27 inch (685mm) .338 Lapua Magnum barrel for the TRG M10 sniper rifle, manufactured by Sako.

name: Sako TRG M10 11 inch handguard assembly
description: An 11 inch long handguard assembly for the TRG M10 sniper rifle, equipped with a Finnish interface for mounting additional equipment. Manufactured by Sako.

name: Sako TRG M10 M-LOK 15 inch handguard assembly
description: A 15 inch long handguard assembly for the TRG M10 sniper rifle, equipped with an M-LOK interface for mounting additional equipment. Manufactured by Sako.

name: Opened case
description: This case contains several sealed boxes.

name: Contraband box
description: A box containing contraband cargo from Peacekeeper. Opening it might not be a good idea.

name: Sealed box
description: The box is sealed to protect its contents. A multitool is required to open it.

name: Opened box
description: This box can't hold much, but now you can see what's inside.

name: Locked case
description: The contents are unknown, but you'll need a key to open it.

name: ShG-2 assault rocket
description: A 72.5mm thermobaric assault rocket for the RShG-2 rocket launcher.

name: Case key
description: A key suitable for opening most standard cases.

name: 5.11 Tactical RUSH 100 backpack (Black)
description: A tactical backpack with a complex modular system. The arrangement of internal compartments and side straps makes the RUSH 100 a highly versatile backpack that can be adapted to any combat situation.

name: LBT-1476A 3Day Pack (MultiCam Alpine)
description: A medium-size 3-day backpack designed for both military and tourist use. Manufactured by London Bridge Trading. MultiCam Alpine version.

name: 6B47 Ratnik-BSh helmet (EMR Arctic cover)
description: 6B47 is an aramid helmet of Russian origin. As part of the Ratnik program, it is the new standard-issue helmet for most of the Russian Armed Forces. The 6B47 is similar to previous generation helmets such as the 6B7-1M and 6B27. It has equal protection but weighs slightly less, floats in water, and has mounting equipment for lights and night vision devices. The helmet can be fitted with a variety of covers for different environments. Equipped with an arctic EMR camouflage cover.

name: Spiritus Systems Bank Robber chest rig (MultiCam Alpine)
description: An ultra-compact and lightweight chest rig for mobility and comfort. Manufactured by Spiritus Systems. MultiCam Alpine camouflage version, for all your winter LARP needs.

name: PP-19-01 9x19 F5 MFG 50-round drum magazine
description: A PP-19-01 Vityaz 9x19 drum magazine with a 50-round capacity. Manufactured by F5 MFG.

name: Velociraptor polymer handguard
description: A polymer handguard for the Velociraptor assault rifle. A modified version of the Tapco AK handguard based on the Galil AR handguard, designed to be installed over the suppressor shroud, preventing possible injury to the shooter's hands during firing.

name: Aklys Defense Velociraptor .300 Blackout assault rifle
description: A special modification based on the AK assault rifle chambered in .300 Blackout caliber, manufactured by Aklys Defense. It replaces the standard barrel assembly with a modified integrally suppressed barrel, which allowed to achieve a significantly reduced sound signature.

name: Akula push dagger
description: As dangerous as the fish it's named after.

name: 6B13 M assault armor (Christmas Edition)
description: To celebrate Christmas and the New Year, Killa redesigned his body armor. The armor is now more noticeable, but Killa has never been one for cautious reconnaissance.

name: Mystery Ranch Terraframe backpack (Olive Drab)
description: A comfortable and spacious backpack for its volume, it remained popular even in wartime. Judging by the attached antlers, this backpack used to belong to a hunter.

name: Mystery Ranch Terraframe backpack (Christmas Edition)
description: Someone has decorated the standard Terraframe model for Christmas. The weight hasn't changed much, but going into a raid has become somehow... more cheerful?

name: SOK-12 Chaos Titan Quad Rail handguard
description: A lightweight handguard from the Titan Quad Rail System for Saiga shotguns. Manufactured by Chaos.

name: SOK-12 Chaos Titan Quad Rail handguard top cover
description: A handguard top rail for the Titan Quad Rail System, manufactured by Chaos.

name: SOK-12 Chaos Titan receiver top rail
description: A receiver top rail for the Titan Quad Rail System, manufactured by Chaos.

name: Chaos HK Style rear sight
description: A rear sight modeled after the popular Heckler & Koch iron sights, manufactured by Chaos.

name: Chaos HK Style front sight
description: A front sight modeled after the popular Heckler & Koch iron sights, manufactured by Chaos.

name: SOK-12 12ga MD Arms 20-round drum magazine
description: The MD Arms 20-shell drum magazine for SOK-12 and compatible weapons, intended for use with 12/76 or 12/70 shells.

name: Saiga-12K 12ga automatic shotgun
description: A modification of the Saiga-12K smoothbore shotgun, enabling fully automatic fire. Hell of a beast.

name: PNV-57E night vision goggles
description: Despite the fact that this model was manufactured in the 80s, the Soviet quality is still evident. The picture might not be as good as gen 2 or gen 3 night vision, but it's definitely worth its price.

name: AR-15 Magpul B.A.D. Lever bolt release
description: The Battery Assist Device Lever for the AR-15 platform and compatibles. Allows to release the bolt into battery from the right side of the rifle, making it easier to operate the weapon for left-handed shooters. Manufactured by Magpul.

name: Jar of pickles
description: The jar has been sealed either a few months or a few years ago. There's hardly anyone left in the city who would waste time making fresh pickles.

name: Olivier salad box
description: Even during a military conflict, experienced warriors strive to celebrate the holiday. Olivier salad is the mainstay of the New Year's Eve table.

name: Special 40-degree fuel
description: Even gasoline can fail in extreme cold. That is why you have to use something stronger outdoors.

name: SHYSHKA Christmas tree life extender
description: A special product designed for preserving the cut Christmas trees.

name: MTEK FLUX Ballistic helmet (MultiCam Alpine)
description: A version of the MTEK STRIKE helmet with extended modularity. MultiCam Alpine version.

name: MTEK FLUX Ballistic helmet (Olive Drab)
description: A version of the MTEK STRIKE helmet with extended modularity. Olive Drab version.

name: MTEK STRIKE Ballistic helmet (Coyote)
description: A lightweight ergonomic helmet manufactured by MTEK. Coyote version.

name: MTEK STRIKE Ballistic helmet (Coyote/MultiCam Arid)
description: A lightweight ergonomic helmet manufactured by MTEK. Coyote/MultiCam Arid version.

name: Maska-1SCh bulletproof helmet (Christmas Edition)
description: The Maska-1 bulletproof protective helmet appeared in service in 1991 as a replacement for the "Sphere" helmet, designed for use by the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation armed forces. The Maska-1SCh ("Mask-1 Shield") modification features a bulletproof steel faceshield to ensure maximum protection of the user's face. Looks like Killa loves to celebrate Christmas and New Year.

name: What You Seek poster
description: A rare What You Seek poster. Only the most hardcore USEC operators can get it.

name: I Bear Loot poster
description: A rare I Bear Loot poster. Very few BEAR operators can get one of these.

name: Girl poster
description: A simple poster of a girl. Perfect for a rest area.

name: Girl poster
description: A simple poster of a girl. A little weathered in some spots, but still pleasing to the eye.

name: Girl poster
description: A simple poster of a girl. So simple that every man in Tarkov had probably seen it at least once.

name: Girl poster
description: A simple poster of a girl. Not perfect condition, but it's doubtful you could find a better one.

name: Girl poster
description: A rare poster of a girl. It is said that someone pawned five gold teeth for one of these. Who they used to belong to is not stated.

name: Special girl poster
description: A poster that has truly become legendary. Only a few people have one of these.

name: Arena poster
description: A blatant advertisement for making money in the Arena. Many Tarkov citizens were tempted by the quick money, despite risking death.

name: Bison vs Undertaker poster
description: A poster from the Arena. It depicts the at the time legendary gladiators. So many Scavs came to see them fight that there weren't enough seats in the stands. Nowadays, nobody even remembers who won.

name: Arena poster
description: A poster advertising making money in the Arena. Sure, you can make money, but you can also die.

name: Killa and Tagilla poster
description: A poster with Killa and Tagila as anime girls. If only they were real.

name: Alex Green poster
description: A poster of the avant-garde composer Alex Green. His music is multifaceted and unique, so much so that the world's leading media wrote about him. People used to pay huge sums of money to visit his concerts.

name: Things Sure Are Strange poster
description: A rare poster of the movie which was never released. Director N. Tankovsky said in an interview that the story would be about a young security guard who began to notice mystical strange things going on in Tarkov.

name: TerraGroup Labs advertisement
description: At one point, the whole Tarkov was flooded with advertisements like this. But for some reason this particular poster is subtly different.

name: Geneburn concert advertisement
description: A rare poster. The concert was held overseas. Why were these posters put up all over Tarkov? No one knows to this day, but conspiracy theories are rampant.

name: Exodus poster
description: A regular poster of yet another movie from the director A. Bambetov.

name: Den of Wolves poster
description: A regular poster for the unreleased movie Den of Wolves. Nothing special, just a wolf.

name: Highway poster
description: An unknown artist tried to envision what a highway will look like in 2028. What is it: a flight of fancy or a subtle warning?

name: Hell or Highwater poster
description: A poster for the movie Hell or Highwater. The big screens never ran it, but Tarkov still has enough of these posters left to use as decoration.

name: Gunfight poster
description: A poster for the action thriller Gunfight from the studio Battle Star. Years ago, cinemas used to have massive waiting lines for movie. Now all that's left are the posters. It's a nice reminder of the old days.

name: Last Flight poster
description: The thriller Last Flight did not win any awards, but the box office collected a decent amount of cash. The director of the movie, Yulin Kontorsky, must have been overjoyed.

name: Spooky Movie poster
description: The studio Bubble Step did a pretty good job on their debut horror film Spooky Movie. Too bad they didn't have enough imagination for the title.

name: Vasily poster
description: The movie Vasily from the legendary director Nikita Bayanov. It held the box office lead for 28 weeks, owing in no small part to its deep and unusual plot.

name: RUN poster
description: The poster is not wordy, but straightforward. It'll look great at the front door. Or the exit door?

name: Sharpshooter poster
description: The movie Sharpshooter never came out. A real shame. The poster's kinda stylish.

name: The Ambush poster
description: A poster of the movie The Ambush. Although, in the end, the audience didn't see anything other than posters.

name: The Hunted poster
description: A poster for the unreleased movie The Hunted. Something about this style reminds of... A sequel to another unreleased project?

name: USEC poster
description: A poster of the unreleased movie USEC. It seems that this is how they wanted to fill the ranks of PMC operatives.

name: Minefield map (Reserve)
description: Someone had sketched a hand-drawn diagram of the perimeter of the Federal Reserve military base in its northwestern part. According to the notes, there is a gap in the minefield that could be used for a safe exfil.

name: Minefield map (Lighthouse)
description: Someone was preparing to assault the water treatment plant and had marked out the optimal routes to bypass the minefields. One of the routes goes toward the bay. Looks like there's a safe exfil route from the coast.

name: Minefield map (Woods)
description: Someone has hand-drawn a diagram of the minefield next to the railroad in the nature reserve area. Apparently, you can safely exfil from Priozersk near the railroad bridge.

name: Note with code word Voron
description: It seems that "Voron" is some kind of cipher or code. If someone has manipulated the exfils from Customs, they must have left access only for their own. The question is, where are these exits?

name: Note with code word Onyx
description: “Onyx”. If it's not a random scribble, then it's some kind of code. Perhaps one of the Scavs has found a new exfil route out of the city, but only allows access to their own. In a densely built environment, a reliable escape route must be underground.

name: Note with code word Adaptation
description: There's only one word on the note: “Adaptation”. Looks like a code word. If someone found a new exfil route out of the TerraGroup HQ area, they must have placed their men nearby to keep anyone from the outside from getting to the new exit. In that case, the code would help distinguish friend from foe.

name: Note with code word Ark
description: The word “Ark” hardly needs to be taken literally. It's more like a code word. There are quite a few locked doors under the Polikhim Factory, leading deeper into the catacombs. Perhaps someone will open the door for you if you know the code word.

name: Note with code word Heartbeat
description: Someone wrote the word “Heartbeat” on a torn piece of paper. Sounds like one of Sanitar's weird pranks. Or perhaps a code word? If his men have their own exfil routes off Shoreline, they must be using a system of key phrases or signals. Maybe this note will make you look like one of their own.

name: Elf hat
description: Usually these hats ring loudly with each head movement. Looks like someone got all the bells out of it beforehand.

name: Hat with horns
description: A Christmas hat with horns. It won't protect you from gunshots, but it can distract your opponent for a split second. Sometimes that's all that matters.

name: Balaclava (White)
description: In normal conditions, this balaclava would be too visible. But in winter it becomes essential, especially in rough terrain.

name: Dogtag BEAR
description: A special army dogtag with rubber sides serving the purpose of quickly identifying the wounded and deceased in combat. An indicator of the PMC operative's status.

name: Dogtag BEAR
description: A special stainless steel army dogtag serving the purpose of quickly identifying the wounded and deceased in combat. Available only to the most experienced PMC operatives.

name: RSP-30 reactive signal cartridge (Firework)
description: RSP-30 is a reactive signal cartridge for commanding and maintaining squad interaction. Multi-star rocket cartridges are used as flares.

name: Signal flare (New Year)
description: Signal flare (New Year)

name: Aklys Defense Velociraptor .300 Blackout assault rifle Default
Secure container Kappa (Desecrated)
description: A secret TerraGroup invention that has fallen into the hands of the cultists.

name: Ballistic plate case
description: A spacious case for storing ballistic plates.

name: .50 AE Copper Solid ammo pack (20 pcs)
description: A pack of .50 AE Copper Solid ammo, 20 rounds.

name: .50 AE FMJ ammo pack (20 pcs)
description: A pack of .50 AE FMJ ammo, 20 rounds.

description: A pack of .50 AE JHP ammo, 20 rounds.

name: .50 AE Hawk JSP ammo pack (20 pcs)
description: A pack of .50 AE Hawk JSP ammo, 20 rounds.

name: 6.8x51mm SIG FMJ ammo pack (20 pcs)
description: A box of 6.8x51mm SIG FMJ cartridges, 20 pieces.

name: 6.8x51mm SIG Hybrid ammo pack (20 pcs)
description: A box of 6.8x51mm SIG Hybrid cartridges, 20 pieces.

name: SOK-12 Kiba Arms Zombie Custom dust cover
description: A receiver dust cover for the SOK-12 shotgun, modernized by Kiba Arms.

name: Rooster mask
description: A children's mask stylized as a rooster. In the realities of Tarkov, it probably looks intimidating. Or not. As if there weren't enough mercs with cringy plastic skull masks already.

name: Cipollino mask
description: It looks like this mask was taken from a warehouse with props for a play based on a G. Rodari story.

name: Aybolit mask
description: A mask depicting one of the best doctors of all time.

name: Fox mask
description: These kinds of masks are often seen at kids' parties. But this one also fits an adult.

name: Grinch mask
description: A mask of someone who hates Christmas.

name: Hare mask
description: A common hare mask. It is unclear just who and why made a copy of this mask to fit an adult.

name: Astronomer mask
description: A stargazer mask with a cap worn by astronomers from children's fairy tales.

name: MPX GEN 2 ambidextrous charging handle
description: An ambidextrous charging handle with two latches for the second generation of the MPX SMG. Manufactured by SIG Sauer.

name: SB Tactical MPX Pistol Stabilizing Brace
description: A brace stock for MPX. Manufactured by SB Tactical.

name: MPX 9x19 Ronin Arms 4.75 inch Ported SD Barrel
description: A 4.75 inch ported barrel from the MPX-SD conversion kit designed for installation of the special suppressor. Manufactured by Ronin Arms.

name: MPX 9x19 Ronin Arms 6.75 inch Ported SD Barrel
description: A 6.75 inch ported barrel from the MPX-SD conversion kit designed for installation of the special suppressor. Manufactured by Ronin Arms.

name: MPX 9x19 Ronin Arms 8 inch SD Suppressor
description: An 8 inch suppressor from the MPX-SD conversion kit designed for installation over the custom ported barrel. Manufactured by Ronin Arms.

name: MPX 9x19 Ronin Arms 12 inch SD Suppressor
description: A 12 inch suppressor from the MPX-SD conversion kit designed for installation over the custom ported barrel. Manufactured by Ronin Arms.

name: MPX GEN1 4 inch handguard
description: A 4 inch handguard for the first generation of the SIG Sauer MPX SMG.

name: MPX GEN1 8 inch handguard
description: An 8 inch handguard for the first generation of the SIG Sauer MPX SMG.

name: MPX GEN2 4 inch M-LOK handguard
description: A 4 inch handguard for the second generation of the SIG Sauer MPX SMG equipped with an M-LOK interface for installation of additional devices and accessories.

name: MPX GEN2 8 inch M-LOK handguard
description: An 8 inch handguard for the second generation of the SIG Sauer MPX SMG equipped with an M-LOK interface for installation of additional devices and accessories.

name: MPX GEN2 6 inch M-LOK handguard
description: A 6 inch handguard for the second generation of the SIG Sauer MPX SMG equipped with an M-LOK interface for installation of additional devices and accessories.

name: Khorovod armband
description: An armband by which the participants of the Khorovod can recognize each other. Without it, you cannot be part of the celebration.

name: Armband (Prestige 1)
description: This armband will help demonstrate your status in Tarkov.

name: Armband (Prestige 2)
description: These armbands are only for the best of the best.

name: Leupold Mark 5HD 5-25x56mm 35mm riflescope (FDE)
description: The Mark 5HD 5-25x56 riflescope is known for being a lighter and more efficient optic than other scopes in its class. Featuring optical glass, full multi-coated lenses and an advanced light management system, the scope offers low-glare, high-contrast imaging. Installed on 35mm ring mounts. Manufactured by Leupold. Flat Dark Earth version.

name: Leupold Mark IMS 35mm ring scope mount
description: A 35mm scope mount for installation on Picatinny rails. Manufactured by Leupold.

name: KAC MWS Bipod Adapter
description: A mount allows installation of Harris bipods on standard Picatinny handguards. Manufactured by Knight's Armament Company.

name: AKMS FAB Defense M4-AKMS P stock adapter
description: A buttstock adapter for the AKMS automatic rifle. Allows to install Com-Spec and Mil-Spec buttstocks on the weapon. Made of durable anodized aluminum. Manufactured by FAB Defense.

name: AR-15 5.56x45 Beta C-Mag 100-round drum magazine
description: A 100-round double drum magazine for the AR-15 platform weapons. Manufactured by Beta Company.

name: UZI 9x19 Beta C-Mag 100-round drum magazine
description: A 100-round double drum magazine for the UZI submachine gun. The magazine modification is equipped with a transparent plastic cover that allows to check the ammo count. Manufactured by Beta Company.

name: M9A3 9x19 CX4 30-round magazine
description: A 30-round 9x19 magazine for the Beretta M9A3 pistol.

name: FN SCAR-H X-17 7.62x51 assault rifle
description: The FN SCAR-H (Special Operations Forces Combat Assault Rifle - Heavy) assault rifle chambered in 7.62x51 NATO rounds, was adopted by the US SOCOM as the Mk 17. Features a side-folding polymer stock and a free-floating, cold hammer-forged Mil-Spec barrel with hardchromed bore. Fully-ambidextrous operating controls instantly adapt the SCAR to any user or any shooting position. The receiver-integrated optical rail plus three accessory rails enable mounting of a wide variety of scopes, electronic sights, tactical lights and lasers. The X-17 lower receiver allows the installation of AR-10 magazines. Manufactured by Fabrique Nationale Herstal and X Products.

name: AR-10 7.62x51 X Products X-25 50-round drum magazine
description: A 50-round 7.62x51 drum magazine for the AR-10 platform weapons. Manufactured by X Products.

name: RFB Quad Rail 3 inch mount
description: A 3 inch quad rail mount for the RFB rifle, allowing the installation of additional tactical equipment. Manufactured by Kel-Tec.

name: AR-15 DoubleStar ACE ARFX Skeleton Stock
description: The lightweight ACE ARFX Skeleton Stock provides comfort, balance and aesthetics. Fits both the Mil-Spec and civilian M/AR platform. Manufactured by DoubleStar.

name: AK AK-EVO stock
description: A new polymer buttstock for the modern AK platform folding weapons. Manufactured by Kalashnikov Concern.

name: Toni System Tactical Barrel Clamp
description: The Tactical Barrel Clamp is designed for mounting on tubular magazines and barrels with a diameter of 20-27 millimeters. Features a rail for attaching additional equipment. Manufactured by Toni System.

name: PP-19-01 Vityaz SAG MK1 M-LOK handguard with gas tube
description: A combined kit consisting of a handguard and a milled gas tube designed to improve the performance of the PP-19-01 Vityaz and the Saiga-9 civilian carbine. The handguard is equipped with an M-LOK interface for installing additional equipment, and the gas tube has a picatinny rail for mounting sights and tactical units. Manufactured by Sureshot Armament Group.

name: Sako TRG M10 .338 LM bolt-action sniper rifle Default
Old house room key
description: A key to one of the rooms in an old house somewhere on the edge of the Priozersk forest. It is said that a person nicknamed Ogryzok used to trade in these parts. He used to sell rare goods including even a steady supply of tank batteries. Yet nothing had long been heard of Ogryzok, and no one knows where he had disappeared to.

name: Company director's room key
description: This key must have been used to lock one of the company offices located in the customs terminal area.

name: SIG MPX 9x19 submachine gun Gen.2 PDW
AK 5.56x45 Molot Arms 45-round magazine
description: A 45-round 5.56x45 polymer magazine for AK. Manufactured by Molot Arms.

name: Cyclone Shakhin mount
description: A Weaver mount for installing the Shakhin thermal scope. Manufactured by Central Research Institute Cyclone.

name: Cyclone Shakhin 3.7x thermal scope
description: A 3.7x thermal scope manufactured by Central Research Institute Cyclone.

name: Cyclone Shakhin scope eyecup
description: A rubber eyecup for the Shakhin thermal scope. Manufactured by Central Research Institute Cyclone.

name: Dogtag USEC
description: A special stainless steel army dogtag serving the purpose of quickly identifying the wounded and deceased in combat. Available only to the most experienced PMC operatives.

name: Dogtag USEC
description: A special army dogtag with rubber sides serving the purpose of quickly identifying the wounded and deceased in combat. An indicator of the PMC operative's status.

description: A box of 20/70 TSS Armor Piercing Slug cartridges, 25 pieces.

name: 20/70 Dangerous Game Slug ammo pack (25 pcs)
description: A box of 20/70 Dangerous Game Slug cartridges, 25 pieces.

name: 7.62x51mm M80A1
description: A 7.62x51mm NATO M80A1 cartridge with a 124 grain armor-piercing copper jacket bullet with an exposed hardened steel penetrator, in a stainless steel casing. Designed as a replacement for the M80 cartridge to improve the armor penetration and ballistics of the cartridge as part of a program to eliminate the use of lead in small arms ammunition in the U.S. Army.

name: 7.62x51mm M80A1 ammo pack (20 pcs)
description: A box of 7.62x51mm M80A1 cartridges, 20 pieces.

name: RShG-2 72.5mm rocket launcher
description: A single-use 72.5mm rocket-propelled grenade launcher, designed to engage enemy personnel in open terrain, field shelters, and various types of structures. Manufactured by NPO Bazalt.

name: Tagilla's welding mask "ZABEY"
description: Judging by this mask, the Labyrinth had severely affected Tagilla's mental state, making him even more unhinged and bloodthirsty. Who thought he could be any more crazy?

name: Valve handwheel
description: A massive handwheel removed from some kind of valve. It must have been used to regulate the water or gas supply in the Knossos underground facilities.

name: Last Breath poster
description: There's no escape from the Minotaur's grasp. The only thing left to do is to take the last deep breath and hold on as long as possible.

name: Final Moment poster
description: Looking at this poster, you realize the sheer terror that the Minotaur's victims felt before they died.

name: Taurus poster
description: This poster embodies the nature of the Minotaur. Brutality, thirst for murder, and blood. Rivers of blood.

name: Tark Souls poster
description: This poster shows the Minotaur being slain by a warrior from the Labyrinth. Very few people have witnessed such a scene with their own eyes.

name: Knossos LLC facility key
description: A worn office door key marked "Knossos LLC". Probably used to open utility rooms or other premises belonging to Knossos.

name: Labrys access keycard
description: A keycard to one of Knossos facilities. The design references the Minotaur mythos, but it's somewhat strange there are no Minotaur theme parks in Tarkov.

name: Labrys research notes
description: The documents are encrypted, but appear to contain research notes on some kind of technology or weapon. The records mention the name “Item 1156”.

name: Nailhead figurine
description: A limited edition Tarko figurine. What's more strange: the pale skin or the nails stuck in his head? It looks like this poor guy has experienced the full spectrum of human pain.

name: Petya Crooker figurine
description: A limited edition Tarko figurine. A creepy dude with a disfigured face and blades on his arm. Doing Obdolbos would give you nightmares.

name: Count Bloodsucker figurine
description: A limited edition Tarko figurine. Count Bloodsucker wouldn't have lasted more than a couple days in Tarkov. Sucking blood is cool and all, but does it work against flashbangs and .308?

name: Xenoalien figurine
description: A limited edition Tarko figurine. Looks like a monster with a disproportionately elongated head and a double mouth. Totally "Alien" (good one) to the Tarko universe.

name: Pointy guy figurine
description: A limited edition Tarko figurine. This funny little character is wearing something like a pyramid on his head. A character like this could only exist in a fictional world, along with zombies and other monsters.

name: Chained Labrys
description: A two-handed axe made out of a sewer hatch... With that weight, a single blow is enough to split a skull, whether the blade is sharp or not.

name: Key 01
description: An old key, the markings are unreadable. Could be useful for surviving the Labyrinth.

name: Key 02
description: This key probably opens some kind of an old lock. The number engraving has been practically scratched off. Could be useful for surviving the Labyrinth.

name: Key 03
description: The number engraving is barely recognizable on the weathered metal. Could be useful for surviving the Labyrinth.

name: Key 04
description: The engraving on this key is barely readable: it's either the number 4 or the Russian letter Ч. Could be useful for surviving the Labyrinth.

name: Observation room key
description: A key that opens one of the personnel workstation rooms in the Labyrinth. That room may have something to do with the research that took place in the Labyrinth.

name: Torture room key
description: An old key that would be more suitable for a shabby lock on a grate or fence than a modern door.

name: Corpse room key
description: An old key that has a strong odor of death. Probably opens a morgue or a room where bodies were kept.

name: Labyrinth key
description: A key that opens a certain room in the Labyrinth. There's no telling what might be inside.

name: Atomic Defense CQCM ballistic mask (Smile)
description: Atomic Defense's CQCM ballistic mask provides protection against short-range weapons including pistols, shotguns and knives. Someone has customized this one to their liking.

name: Atomic Defense CQCM ballistic mask (Stop Me)
description: Atomic Defense's CQCM ballistic mask provides protection against short-range weapons including pistols, shotguns and knives. Could this writing on it be considered a cry for help?

name: Atomic Defense CQCM ballistic mask (Scars)
description: Atomic Defense's CQCM ballistic mask provides protection against short-range weapons including pistols, shotguns and knives. Scars or ritual symbols - what it depicts is up to you to determine.

name: Atomic Defense CQCM ballistic mask (Target)
description: Atomic Defense's CQCM ballistic mask provides protection against short-range weapons including pistols, shotguns and knives. This reinforced mask covers the wearer's face completely. It's unclear who had the idea to paint a target on it, but that sure is pretty ironic.

name: Atomic Defense CQCM ballistic mask (Skull)
description: Atomic Defense's CQCM ballistic mask provides protection against short-range weapons including pistols, shotguns and knives. Some say the skull is a universal symbol that inspires fear and respect in opponents.

name: Atomic Defense CQCM ballistic mask (Demon)
description: Atomic Defense's CQCM ballistic mask provides protection against short-range weapons including pistols, shotguns and knives. This reinforced mask covers the wearer's face completely. Mom always asked you to smile more, but she hardly expected this.

name: Atomic Defense CQCM ballistic mask (El Día de Muertos)
description: Atomic Defense's CQCM ballistic mask provides protection against short-range weapons including pistols, shotguns and knives. The drawing is applied with a durable paint for true fans of El Día de Muertos, the Day of the Dead.

name: Lower half-mask (MultiCam)
description: A piece of cloth, typically a bandana, covering the face from nose and below, is the most typical attribute of a street gang member. MultiCam camouflage version.

name: Lower half-mask (Zombie)
description: A piece of cloth, typically a bandana, covering the face from nose and below, is the most typical attribute of a street gang member. The zombie print is chosen in hopes of intimidating opponents.

name: Lower half-mask (Moss)
description: A piece of cloth, typically a bandana, covering the face from nose and below, is the most typical attribute of a street gang member. Moss camouflage version.

name: Lower half-mask (El Día de Muertos)
description: A piece of cloth, typically a bandana, covering the face from nose and below, is the most typical attribute of a street gang member. For true fans of El Día de Muertos, the Day of the Dead.

name: Lower half-mask (Wraith)
description: A piece of cloth, typically a bandana, covering the face from nose and below, is the most typical attribute of a street gang member. The print is chosen in hopes of intimidating opponents.

name: Lower half-mask (Balaclavas Green)
description: A piece of green cloth, typically a bandana, covering the face from nose and below, is the most typical attribute of a street gang member. The colorful print will highlight your personality.

name: Lower half-mask (Balaclavas Red)
description: A piece of red cloth, typically a bandana, covering the face from nose and below, is the most typical attribute of a street gang member. The colorful print will highlight your personality.

name: Lower half-mask (Balaclavas)
description: A piece of cloth, typically a bandana, covering the face from nose and below, is the most typical attribute of a street gang member. The colorful print will highlight your personality.

name: Balaclava (Green)
description: A definitive woolen balaclava is not only a head-warmer but soul-warmer too for anyone who is too modest for public heroic deeds. Vibrant green version.

name: Balaclava (Scars)
description: Scars adorn a man, even if they're just on his balaclava.

name: Balaclava (Scratches)
description: The embroidered scratches on this balaclava refer to the worst fight of your life. Or trying to pet a fussy cat.

name: Balaclava (Born to Die)
description: With the embroidery on this balaclava, everyone will know your creed.

name: Balaclava (Not Nice)
description: A definitive woolen balaclava is not only a head-warmer but soul-warmer too for anyone who is too modest for public heroic deeds. The letterings add some flavor.

name: Balaclava (Yellow)
description: Why make face tattoos when you can make them on a mask.

name: Balaclava (Luxury)
description: This balaclava is designed to catch the eye. It's a good thing no one will recognize you with it on.

name: Cold Fear infrared balaclava (Green)
description: A quality balaclava with a special technological material, which ensures maximum warmth in the most severe frosts. Green version. Or a Ranger Green version. Or an Olive Drab version. Or a Taiga Green version. Or an Army Green version. Or a Deep Forest Green version.

name: Cold Fear infrared balaclava (SBEU)
description: A quality balaclava with a special technological material, which ensures maximum warmth in the most severe frosts. Very Stylish version.

name: Cold Fear infrared balaclava (Oak)
description: A quality balaclava with a special technological material, which ensures maximum warmth in the most severe frosts. Hunting camo version.

name: Cold Fear infrared balaclava (Surpat)
description: A quality balaclava with a special technological material, which ensures maximum warmth in the most severe frosts. Surpat camo version.

name: Cold Fear infrared balaclava (DPM Desert)
description: A quality balaclava with a special technological material, which ensures maximum warmth in the most severe frosts. Desert Disruptive Pattern Material version. Drip? Unlimited.

name: Cold Fear infrared balaclava (MultiCam Tropic)
description: A quality balaclava with a special technological material, which ensures maximum warmth in the most severe frosts. MultiCam Tropic version.

name: Cold Fear infrared balaclava (Tiger Stripe)
description: A quality balaclava with a special technological material, which ensures maximum warmth in the most severe frosts. Tiger Stripe camouflage version.

name: Balaclava (Red Nose)
description: A universal balaclava. For those who want to express their individuality and warn both enemies and allies about who you really are.

name: Balaclava (Demon)
description: A universal balaclava. For the true Japanese warriors.

name: Balaclava (Skull)
description: Another balaclava with a skull print for the truest mall ninjas.

name: Balaclava (Fear)
description: Express yourself and intimidate your enemies (or make them cringe) with a yet another skull mask.

name: Balaclava (Yellow Oni)
description: A balaclava with a yellow Oni print.

name: Balaclava (Red Oni)
description: A balaclava with a red Oni print.

name: Balaclava (White Oni)
description: A balaclava with a white Oni print.

name: Balaclava (Smile)
description: A balaclava with a toothy smile print.

name: Neoprene mask (M90 Desert)
description: A lightweight neoprene mask. M90 Desert camouflage version.

name: Neoprene mask (Louise Pitton)
description: A lightweight neoprene mask with a luxury design.

name: Neoprene mask (Lucha Libre)
description: A lightweight neoprene mask with a professional wrestling print.

name: Neoprene mask (Zombie)
description: A lightweight neoprene mask with a zombie print.

name: Neoprene mask (Say Nothing)
description: A lightweight neoprene mask with a unique print. The little symbol on the side looks strangely familiar.

name: Neoprene mask (ONI)
description: A lightweight neoprene mask with an Oni print.

name: Hexatac HPC Plate Carrier (MultiCam)
description: A plate carrier by Hexatac. A minimalistic version designed to be used with chest rigs. MultiCam version.

name: BNTI Kirasa-N body armor (Green)
description: The "Kirasa N" body armor is designed for the army and police special forces of the Russian Federation. The bulletproof vest provides circular protection of the human torso. Elements of the damper provide ventilation of the under armor space and reduce the blunt damage. Green version.

name: FORT Redut-M body armor (SK Woodland)
description: “Redut-M” is a modified version of the well-proven Redut body armor, which is in service of special units of the FSB. The vest is based on advanced technologies in the field of individual armor. Due to the optimized form of armor elements and the outer cover with a special damping-ventilation system, the Redut M armored vest has excellent functional qualities, which facilitates active actions, including those associated with the use of vehicles and in confined spaces. SK Woodland version.

name: HighCom Trooper TFO body armor (Coyote)
description: A plate armor vest by HighCom, popular among USEC PMCs. Coyote version.

name: BBQ-S43 gas torch
description: A portable torch with a limited gas supply. This bad boy is unlikely to burn a hole in the wall, but will do the job on a small metal target.

name: ANA Tactical Alpha chest rig (MultiCam)
description: "Alpha" is a high-quality chest rig that fully meets the military standards for reliability and functionality. The combination of integrated pouches and MOLLE straps provides the means of carrying a large number of necessary equipment. The vest is designed as a classic chest rig. In this type of vest, all the gear is located in the front and side parts, while the back part is comprised of adjustment belts and straps. Manufactured by ANA Tactical. MultiCam camouflage version.

name: BlackRock chest rig (Khaki)
description: A custom-made chest rig for wearing on top of body armor in urban operations. Sturdy and versatile, it features both MOLLE and ALICE attachment systems. Khaki version.

name: Crye Precision AVS plate carrier (MultiCam)
description: The Crye Precision AVS plate carrier equipped with Groin Protector and pouches in assault configuration. MultiCam camouflage version.

name: 5.11 Tactical TacTec plate carrier (Storm)
description: A plate carrier with a set of pouches for use with assault rifles. Manufactured by 5.11 Tactical. Storm color version.

name: Dundukk sport sunglasses (Orange lenses)
description: Modern sunglasses, made in a sporty style. Great for a stylish shootout at the gas station.

name: RayBench Aviator glasses (Green lenses)
description: Legendary mercenary glasses around the world. Wear them if you want to be cool, like Vovan from the hood.

name: Oakley SI M Frame safety glasses (Orange lenses)
description: Ballistic glasses with impact-resistant polycarbonate lenses.

name: Round frame sunglasses (Green lenses)
description: Sunglasses with a round-shaped frame. Cool and stylish!

name: F-1 hand grenade (Reduced delay)
description: The F-1 hand grenade (GRAU Index 57-G-721) is an anti-personnel fragmentation grenade, designed for neutralizing enemy personnel in defensive combat. This version is personally modified by Partisan and has a shortened fuze, intended for explosive tripwires.

name: HighCom Trooper TFO body armor (Coyote) Default
Crye Precision AVS plate carrier (MultiCam) Default
FORT Redut-M body armor (SK Woodland) Default
Locked equipment crate (BattlePass 0)
description: A reward for progress in BattlePass Season 0. It contains various equipment to help you survive and kill in the harsh world of Tarkov. But first, you need to find a way to open this box.

name: Unlocked equipment crate (BattlePass 0)
description: A reward for progress in BattlePass Season 0. It contains various equipment to help you survive and kill in the harsh world of Tarkov. The lock has been crudely broken, which means there are no more obstacles between you and the contents of the box.

name: Key case
description: This case is the ultimate solution to the problem of hoarding various keys in the stash, helping to store them in one place.

name: Ariadne symbol key
description: Someone had made a barely visible mark on this key, resembling a ball of thread. Although, it could have simply been left by careless storage.

name: Tagilla's welding mask "ZABEY" (Replica)
description: Judging by this mask, the Labyrinth had severely affected Tagilla's mental state, making him even more unhinged and bloodthirsty. Who thought he could be any more crazy? It seems that this is merely a replica and cannot be worn. The mask was probably created as a souvenir, intended to remind survivors of their encounter with a ruthless killer.

name: Arena Cup Series balaclava
description: A signature balaclava of the famous Tarkov hip-hop artist with the Arena Cup Series tournament insignia. The artist hasn't performed in Tarkov for quite a while, but their merch has found a new life.

name: Killa fangirl poster
description: This poster shows a Killa fangirl. Despite the scratches on the paper and folding marks, you can tell that the previous owner treasured this poster very much.

name: Grenade girl poster
description: Women are not usually allowed to join BEAR or USEC. But even though the poster is damaged and the paper is sticky in places, it is obvious that this photo is authentic.

name: Unusual leather rig poster
description: It seems unlikely that similar pieces of equipment are available in present-day Tarkov. Judging by the condition of the poster, it was obviously made during peacetime.
